CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1774469468
OL,3,CEx-wife admits 'horrible' messages to
OL,4,Cdrug dealer days before fatal attack
OL,6,FNine people are standing trial,
OL,7,Faccused of charges including murder,
OL,8,Fattempted kidnap and participating in
OL,9,Fthe criminal activities of an
OL,10,Forganised crime group.
OL,12,FThe court has heard the attack was
OL,13,Fallegedly arranged by drug boss Ryan
OL,14,FKennedy, also known as 'Frost', to
OL,15,Fwhom Danny owed around #120,000.
OL,17,FUnder cross-examination at Winchester
OL,18,FCrown Court on Wednesday, Danny's ex-
OL,19,Fwife Paris Wilson accepted that she
OL,20,Fsent 'horrible' messages to Danny on
OL,21,F17 February.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1774469468
OL,3,CEx-wife admits 'horrible' messages to
OL,4,Cdrug dealer days before fatal attack
OL,6,FThey read: "Don't message me...just
OL,7,Fdrop dead...I'm exhausted by your lies.
OL,9,F"So I hope you and your butters girl
OL,10,Fboth end up with acid in your faces.
OL,11,FNow don't ever message me again."
OL,13,FAsked about the messages in court, Ms
OL,14,FWilson said: "It's horrible. It's a
OL,15,Fhorrible thing to say.
OL,17,F"I had heard that as a threat before.
OL,18,FBut I wasn't party to it being enacted.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1774469468
OL,3,CEx-wife admits 'horrible' messages to
OL,4,Cdrug dealer days before fatal attack
OL,6,F"But yes, I'd heard Frost say he was
OL,7,Fgoing to do things like this to Dan on
OL,8,Fmore than one occasion. I'd heard him
OL,9,Fsay he was going to melt his face off."
OL,11,FJo Martin KC, prosecuting, asked Ms
OL,12,FWilson if she understood the
OL,13,Fconsequences of someone having acid
OL,14,Fthrown in their face.
OL,16,F"I'm not an idiot," Ms Wilson said. "I
OL,17,Fknow that acid would cause significant
OL,18,Fharm to someone.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1774469468
OL,3,CEx-wife admits 'horrible' messages to
OL,4,Cdrug dealer days before fatal attack
OL,6,F"But if I'd known this was
OL,7,Fsignificant, I would have gone and got
OL,8,F(our daughter) away from him."
OL,10,FMs Wilson told the court she had 'no
OL,11,Fcontact' with Frost in the days before
OL,12,Fthe attack on Danny.
OL,14,FParis Wilson denies murder,
OL,15,Fmanslaughter, participating in the
OL,16,Fcriminal activities of an organised
OL,17,Fcrime group, and attempted kidnap.
OL,19,FEight other defendants also all deny
OL,20,Fthe charges. The trial continues.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/5
